deck: I.S. suits are supposed to be compatible only to women. Enters the second male I.S. pilot. How did this happen?
name: Boy Meets Boy

deck: The second male I.S. pilot turns out to be a female posing as a male to further her family's interest.
name: My Roommate is a Young, Blonde Nobleman

description: On the lam from the NYPD, Sara turns to Jake for help, but is Jake in on the conspiracy against her? Meanwhile, Kenneth Irons struggles to stay alive as he spins out a plot to attain the one gruesome elixir that can save him! Irons reveals his true intentions for Sara and the Witchblade
name: Convergence

description: Sara's unlikely protector surfaces with a life-threatening passion to watch over her that leads to irrevocable consequences. Sara has no choice but to accept the destiny that comes with wielding the gauntlet and use it to regain what she has lost. But every gain has its price. True to the words of the Witchblade's past wielders, "Nothing is as it seems". A startling discovery about Dante and his team of corrupt cops lead to a suspenseful showdown between the rising warrior and a band of enemies that she must conquer before her father's killer is revealed
name: Transcendence

description: Time resets, and Sara and Danny are at the Rialto, but Sara turns away, causing great annoyance in Irons, who wanted the Witchblade to bond with her through shedding blood. So he decides to find a new woman to wield the 'Blade, and sets a murderous plot in motion to make it all happen.
name: Emergence

description: Using the powers of the Witchblade, Sara saves the life of her partner, Danny Woo. But when Irons procures an ancient weapon, can she save herself as the battle for the Witchblade turns into a fight to the death?
name: Destiny

description: As Sara and Danny investigate a series of bizarre drug-related murders, rookie detective Jake is pulled into a sting with a questionable cop. Now Sara must learn to use the Witchblade to solve the crime and save Jake before it's too late.
name: Agape

name: Blue Days ~ Red Switch

name: Find Out My Mind

description: Oliver finds out the medicine that is being sent to Glades Memorial is being hijacked by thieves. Without an influx of supplies, the hospital will close. Roy attempts to stop the thieves, but he fails and is arrested by Officer Lance. Oliver gets into a heated battle with China White and her new partner, Ben Turner, AKA the Bronze Tiger, over the supplies. Meanwhile, Laurel makes plans to catch the Arrow, and Thea gives Roy an ultimatum.
name: Identity

description: When Splinter allows his teenage sons, the Mutant Ninja Turtles, to visit the surface for the first time, they discover that the surface world isn't as simple as it first appears.
name: Rise of The Turtles, Part 1

description: Raphael loses his temper when he is insulted by a New Yorker named Vic. When Vic catches the Turtles on video, the Turtles must get the phone back or risk the possibility of their existence becoming widely known.
name: Turtle Temper

description: To prove that Turtles can be friends with humans, Michelangelo uses a social networking site to befriend Chris Bradford, a famous martial artist who is secretly Shredder's top lieutenant.
name: New Friend, Old Enemy

description: When the Turtles sneak out against Splinter's wishes, they battle Baxter Stockman, a deranged inventor in mechanical battle armor.
name: I Think His Name is Baxter Stockman

description: Weary of using his simple bo staff to fight the technologically advanced Kraang, Donatello creates Metalhead, a remote-controlled robot turtle to fight in his place.
name: Metalhead

description: Donatello and April investigate a scientist's disappearance, but discover a conspiracy regarding a bizarre psychic monkey instead.
name: Monkey Brains

description: Leo fears his act of mercy has come back to haunt him when Xever holds a local noodle shop owner hostage.
name: Never Say Xever

description: After April receives a warning from her imprisoned father, she and the Turtles embark on a mission to save him and stop the Kraang from detonating a mutagen bomb in the city.
name: The Gauntlet

description: The Turtles must defend their home in the sewers when Bradford tries to destroy it with a dangerous chemical.
name: Panic In The Sewers

description: When simultaneous threats from the Purple Dragons and Baxter Stockman's mechanical Mousers force the Turtles to split into two groups, Donnie & Mikey must prove that their "B Team" is just as valuable as Leo & Raph's "A Team."
name: Mousers Attack!

deck: The Lost City of Khemir was a city that always depended on robots to get things done. Since all technology has failed, they are unsure what to do. The Darkling Lords convince them to capture the Spectral Knights to be their slaves!
name: The Price of Freedom

series.name: Visionaries: Knights of the Magical Light

deck: After a difficult battle, Feryl is convinced he is useless and leaves the Spectral Knights. The Darkling Lords try to take advantage of that.
name: Feryl Steps Out

series.name: Visionaries: Knights of the Magical Light

description: The disappearances of several industrialists against the environment have intrigued Bruce Wayne's attention to locate Poison Ivy as Batman within Gotham City while he offers Alfred Pennyworth and his date an opportunity to a rejuvenation health spa that leaves the couple revived , but not completely human, when Batman takes further investigation.
name: Eternal Youth

description: When Splinter allows his teenage sons, the Mutant Ninja Turtles, to visit the surface for the first time, they discover that the surface world isn't as simple as it first appears.
name: Rise of the Turtles, Part 2

description: Michelangelo befriends an unstable mutant alligator who possesses a strange piece of Kraang technology, but the other Turtles aren't sure whether Leatherhead is a friend or a foe.
name: It Came From The Depths

description: The Turtles must face off against a new enemy, The Rat King, who threatens not only to take control of the city, but Splinter's mind as well.
name: I, Monster

description: Leonardo, tired of Raphael's constant criticism, lets his brother try his hand at leadership for a while. Meanwhile, Leonardo meets a beautiful and dangerous female ninja who tries to lure Leonardo to the dark side.
name: New Girl In Town

description: The Turtles get their first taste of high school when April's school project draws Kraang attention.
name: The Alien Agenda

description: The Turtles meet their first fanboy when a teenage wannabe hero decides to fight crime and dress up as "The Pulverizer."
name: The Pulverizer

deck: The team brings a mutated squirrel back to their lair, but it starts multiplying! Now the Turtles are tasked with hunting down these mutants before they can escape into the city's streets!
description: While tracking mutagen, the Turtles bring a mutated squirrel back to the lair. When it starts multiplying, the Turtles must hunt the squirrel mutants and prevent them escaping into the city.
name: Invasion of the Squirrelanoids

description: Based of Ultimate Spider-man #66-67
name: Freaky

deck: Willow discovers Oz is a werewolf.
description:
Cordelia takes her daddy's car and drives Xander to the woods to make out. They are interrupted by a werewolf. Now Buffy's plate is full; not only is Angel still active, now she has to contend with this latest pressing threat to Sunnydale.

Xander immediately suspects Larry, the school bully, and is determined to confront him.

Meanwhile, Willow, baffled by Oz's on again off again romantic intentions, is determined to confront him.
name: Phases

deck: Xander gets Amy to cast a spell, which makes all the woman fall in loved with him.
description: Giles worries about Buffy's safety since Angel has a history of attacks on Valentine's Day. His fear is legitimized when Angel leaves a box of roses for Buffy with the ominous message "soon". Meanwhile, Cordelia is ostracized for dating Xander and breaks up with him on Valentine's Day. Xander discovers that Amy Madison is a witch, and blackmails her into casting a love spell on Cordelia for him. Things don't go as planned.
name: Bewitched, Bothered and Bewildered

deck: Angel begins to terrorize Buffy and her friends, leaving drawings in their bedrooms, killing Willow's fish, and ultimately attacking and killing Jenny Calendar. Buffy and Giles become extremely aggressive when their families are threatened.
description:
The episode is narrated by Angel who discusses "passion". In his passion he sets out to stalk and terrorize Buffy. Since he's previously been invited into Buffy's house, Willow's house, and Giles' apartment (and Cordelia's car), he strikes at them in those places, as well as at the school where a sign inviting entry to those seeking knowledge is sufficient.

Jenny Calendar intends to return Angel's soul, but Drusilla has a prophetic vision that tips him off, so Angel proceeds to Ms. Calendar's office to destroy her computer and kill her. He leaves her body along with champagne and roses in Giles' apartment.
name: Passion

deck: Buffy must stop a demon that is attacking children in Hospital.
description: Already suffering from the flu, a weakened Buffy gets into a skirmish with Angel while on patrol. She escapes with the help of the "Scooby Gang", but collapses and they have to take her to the emergency room. While recovering she discovers that children in the hospital are being preyed upon by a supernatural entity.
name: Killed by Death

deck: A demon steals the Book of Shadows. The charmed ones must find the book and destroy the demon.
name: Witch Trial
